  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improvement of livelihoods through honey bee farming in Bangladesh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to improve the income, livelihoods and living conditions of the most disadvantaged farmers, including women and Adivasi (indigenous) families, through bee keeping and increased crop production by pollination. The project will directly target 250 disadvantaged farmers (147 women) in Birol sub-district, Dinajpur district, northern Bangladesh. The project will reach a total of 1,250 people including the farmer&#x2019;s family members.</narrative>
  </description>
